      "The Baku main straight — from Turn 16 to Turn 1 — measures approximately 2.2 kilometres, making it the longest straight of any circuit currently on the Formula 1 calendar; cars reach speeds approaching 370 km/h.",
      "The 2017 Azerbaijan Grand Prix produced one of the most controversial moments in modern F1 when Sebastian Vettel deliberately drove into Lewis Hamilton during a safety car period, earning a 10-second stop-go penalty.",
      "Turn 8, the castle section, is so narrow that drivers have less than 40 centimetres of clearance on each side of their car — any deviation from the ideal line results in immediate contact with the medieval walls.",
      "The 2021 Azerbaijan Grand Prix ended with Max Verstappen's tyre exploding at nearly 300 km/h while he was leading on the final lap; he crashed heavily into the barrier, ending a race he seemed destined to win.",
      "Sergio Pérez has an extraordinary record at Baku, winning the 2021 race after Verstappen's crash and performing consistently well here, earning him the nickname 'The Prince of Baku'.",
      "The circuit is built around the Old City of Baku, a UNESCO World Heritage Site — racing at this circuit involves Formula 1 cars passing through streets that have existed for over a thousand years."
