      "Lusail was designed and primarily used as a motorcycle racing circuit — its flowing, long-radius corners are quite different from typical F1 circuits and create unique load patterns on car tyres that teams are still learning to manage.",
      "Qatar's deal with Formula 1, signed in 2021, guarantees Grand Prix racing in the country until 2032 — one of the longest contracts in the sport's history.",
      "The circuit is completely flat, reflecting the desert topography of the region, which makes aerodynamic efficiency rather than mechanical grip the dominant performance factor.",
      "Max Verstappen's 2023 lap record of 1:24.319 was set during qualifying for the Sprint race, a format which allows for a focused single-lap performance without the tyre management considerations of a race stint.",
