      "The Autodromo Internacional do Algarve near Portimão in southern Portugal is one of the most visually spectacular and technically unique circuits in motorsport, carved into the dramatic rolling hills of the Algarve region with extraordinary elevation changes that create a constant sensation of the car rising and falling through the corners. The circuit hosted its first Formula 1 races in 2020 and 2021 after decades as a highly regarded test and racing facility for other categories. Its flowing, challenging layout — featuring several blind corners and dramatic gradient changes — was immediately praised by drivers and fans as the circuit they most wished to see on the permanent calendar.",
